211
00:14:16,200 --> 00:14:17,600
She praised you, you know.

212
00:14:17,600 --> 00:14:19,800
I don't need praise. I need the money.

213
00:14:19,800 --> 00:14:21,200
Take care of that for me.

214
00:14:21,200 --> 00:14:24,500
And if there's nothing else, don't call again.

215
00:14:34,100 --> 00:14:37,800
This is a painting by Naan Bua Phan, a Tai Lue (ethnic group northern TH, Laos, China) artist.

216
00:14:37,800 --> 00:14:40,600
The outfit worn by Yaa (Grandma) Man is traditional Tai Lue formal wear,

217
00:14:40,600 --> 00:14:43,200
while Puu (Grandpa) Man wears Burmese attire.

218
00:14:43,200 --> 00:14:45,160
If we look closely at Granny Man's outfit,

219
00:14:45,160 --> 00:14:47,800
the color palette uses red, blue,

220
00:14:47,800 --> 00:14:53,700
dark brown, and black tones we often see in Thai woven textiles.

221
00:14:53,700 --> 00:14:55,200
I think this painting

222
00:14:55,200 --> 00:14:59,900
reflects the values and evolution of love stories through time beautifully.

223
00:15:00,900 --> 00:15:06,600
They say if a couple wants their love to be strong and lasting,

224
00:15:06,600 --> 00:15:08,860
the man should whisper his love to the woman

225
00:15:08,860 --> 00:15:11,600
and make a wish in front of this mural.

226
00:15:13,300 --> 00:15:17,000
You really know a lot about traditional art.

227
00:15:17,000 --> 00:15:21,400
When I first joined, you teased me for only liking old stuff.

228
00:15:21,400 --> 00:15:24,800
Now you know even more than I do.

229
00:15:24,800 --> 00:15:26,600
True.

230
00:15:26,600 --> 00:15:33,500
Well, I started learning when we began this project.

231
00:15:33,500 --> 00:15:35,000
Right.

232
00:15:35,000 --> 00:15:38,800
There are a lot of other corners and murals I want everyone to check out.

233
00:15:38,800 --> 00:15:40,800
They might be useful details for our designs.

234
00:15:40,800 --> 00:15:42,400
Hey, that spot over there looks beautiful.

235
00:15:42,400 --> 00:15:44,400
Take a photo there. Come on.

236
00:15:44,400 --> 00:15:46,100
- P'Moo, hurry up!
- Okay.

237
00:15:53,420 --> 00:15:55,573
Do you like this kind of artwork?

238
00:15:55,573 --> 00:15:59,890
I like artists who use art to tell love stories through their brushstrokes.

239
00:15:59,890 --> 00:16:02,750
I like artists who use art to tell love stories through their brushstrokes.

240
00:16:02,753 --> 00:16:05,187
It's kind of romantic, Khun Tul.

241
00:16:12,153 --> 00:16:13,740
Pete.

