264
00:18:01,700 --> 00:18:03,000
Kaew, Kaew!

265
00:18:03,000 --> 00:18:04,300
Your P'Cake is awake!

266
00:18:04,300 --> 00:18:07,800
- Yes!
- Hurry up! Your P'Cake's awake!

267
00:18:09,300 --> 00:18:11,200
P'Cake!

268
00:18:11,200 --> 00:18:13,200
It's Kaew, P'Cake!

269
00:18:13,200 --> 00:18:14,700
- Cake, Sweetie!
- P'Cake!

270
00:18:14,700 --> 00:18:17,300
- Bpaa, P'Cake is awake!
- Cake!

271
00:18:17,300 --> 00:18:19,967
- Kaew, Kaew, go get my phone, quick, Dear!
- Oh, right! I'm on it!

272
00:18:20,000 --> 00:18:21,700
Cake...

273
00:18:21,700 --> 00:18:24,300
I'm so happy, Sweetie.

274
00:18:25,793 --> 00:18:27,947
- Yes, Bpaa?
- Cream.

275
00:18:27,947 --> 00:18:30,527
Cake woke up, Sweetie.

276
00:18:30,527 --> 00:18:32,467
Really, Bpaa?

277
00:18:32,467 --> 00:18:34,693
Can I talk to her?

278
00:18:34,693 --> 00:18:36,233
Not yet.

279
00:18:36,233 --> 00:18:39,360
She just woke up, but she's still very dazed.

280
00:18:39,360 --> 00:18:42,873
Her body doesn't seem fully responsive yet.

281
00:18:42,873 --> 00:18:44,820
I tried talking to her just now,

282
00:18:44,820 --> 00:18:49,100
but she can barely move or speak.

283
00:18:49,100 --> 00:18:51,107
Is Cake paralyzed, Bpaa?

284
00:18:51,107 --> 00:18:52,980
I'm not sure yet.

285
00:18:52,980 --> 00:18:58,440
But tomorrow, I'll take her to the hospital for a full check-up.

286
00:18:58,440 --> 00:19:01,620
Then can I come with you?

287
00:19:01,620 --> 00:19:03,227
Wait, wait, would that be okay, Dear?

288
00:19:03,227 --> 00:19:05,787
What if someone sees you?

289
00:19:05,787 --> 00:19:09,093
I think it's safer if I go alone.

290
00:19:09,093 --> 00:19:12,300
I want to hear the results for myself, Bpaa.

291
00:19:12,300 --> 00:19:14,400
All right then.

292
00:19:14,400 --> 00:19:18,900
Tomorrow, I'll have the ambulance come pick up Cake from home.

293
00:19:18,900 --> 00:19:20,600
Okay.

294
00:19:20,600 --> 00:19:22,600
See you, Bpaa.

295
00:19:32,580 --> 00:19:34,447
What results are you waiting for?

296
00:19:35,147 --> 00:19:37,563
Is someone sick, Khun Cream?

297
00:19:39,180 --> 00:19:40,893
A relative.

298
00:19:40,893 --> 00:19:42,830
They're not feeling well,

299
00:19:42,830 --> 00:19:45,320
and they don't have anyone to take them to the doctor.

300
00:19:46,580 --> 00:19:48,680
Want me to come with you?

301
00:19:49,473 --> 00:19:51,340
It's okay.

302
00:19:51,340 --> 00:19:56,220
You have so much to do; I don't want to bother you.

303
00:19:56,220 --> 00:19:58,360
Thank you, though.

304
00:19:58,360 --> 00:20:01,447
Shall we go take a look over there?

305
00:20:01,447 --> 00:20:03,767
Let's go. This way, please.

306
00:20:20,720 --> 00:20:22,500
Everyone, see you at the office tomorrow.

307
00:20:22,500 --> 00:20:24,687
- Yes.
- Got it.

308
00:20:24,687 --> 00:20:26,587
Khun Cream. Khun Cream.

309
00:20:26,587 --> 00:20:28,733
Khun Pete? What are you doing here?

310
00:20:28,733 --> 00:20:30,600
I need to talk to you about something important.

311
00:20:30,600 --> 00:20:33,200
The police couldn't reach you so they called me about the case.

312
00:20:33,200 --> 00:20:34,980
Thanks. I'll call them back myself.

313
00:20:34,980 --> 00:20:36,370
Excuse me.

314
00:20:36,373 --> 00:20:38,493
Khun Cream... Khun Cream, please.

315
00:20:38,493 --> 00:20:40,407
- She said she has something to do.
- Hey!

316
00:20:40,407 --> 00:20:42,067
What does this have to do with you?

317
00:20:42,067 --> 00:20:43,647
This is between me and Khun Cream.

318
00:20:43,647 --> 00:20:45,193
You're just an outsider. Stay out of it.

319
00:20:45,193 --> 00:20:47,680
Khun Cream told me you lied.

320
00:20:47,680 --> 00:20:49,427
She doesn't feel anything for you.

321
00:20:49,427 --> 00:20:51,340
But I still do.

322
00:20:51,340 --> 00:20:54,000
From then until now.

323
00:20:56,260 --> 00:20:57,740
Ai Pete.

324
00:21:01,653 --> 00:21:03,260
Hey, Wine.

325
00:21:03,260 --> 00:21:05,113
Yes, I've arrived.

326
00:21:06,107 --> 00:21:08,880
No need to cancel the board. I'll head back right after this.

327
00:21:14,927 --> 00:21:16,547
Cake.

328
00:21:17,160 --> 00:21:18,480
Cake.

329
00:21:18,480 --> 00:21:19,887
Cake.

330
00:21:19,887 --> 00:21:23,000
I'm so happy you opened your eyes, Cake!

331
00:21:23,000 --> 00:21:24,607
Cake.

332
00:21:24,607 --> 00:21:27,280
It's okay, you'll get better.

333
00:21:27,280 --> 00:21:29,940
You've always been strong.

334
00:21:29,940 --> 00:21:32,260
I'll go grab something from the car, okay?

335
00:21:32,260 --> 00:21:33,960
I'll be back in a sec.

336
00:21:33,960 --> 00:21:37,460
Oh, I'll grab a blanket too. Just in case it's cold in the hospital.

337
00:21:37,460 --> 00:21:40,233
Watch her for me, sweetie.

338
00:21:53,520 --> 00:21:55,320
- Khun Cream.
- Khun Pete?

339
00:21:55,320 --> 00:21:57,581
Did you follow me here?

340
00:21:57,581 --> 00:21:59,353
I'm sorry.

341
00:21:59,353 --> 00:22:02,080
I have something important I want to tell you.

342
00:22:02,080 --> 00:22:04,373
When you were in Nan, I called you several times and you didn't answer.

343
00:22:04,373 --> 00:22:06,347
And just now, your phone was turned off again.

344
00:22:06,347 --> 00:22:08,680
The police have a lead on the person who attacked you.

345
00:22:08,680 --> 00:22:10,520
They want you to come to the station.

346
00:22:10,520 --> 00:22:14,120
Thank you so much, but could you head back first?

347
00:22:14,120 --> 00:22:15,833
I'll go to the station myself.

348
00:22:15,833 --> 00:22:16,893
And this house...

349
00:22:16,893 --> 00:22:19,620
- Whose is it?
- My relative's house.

350
00:22:20,267 --> 00:22:22,940
- Let me help.
- No need.

351
00:22:22,940 --> 00:22:24,787
I can handle it myself.

352
00:22:24,787 --> 00:22:26,827
Please just go back.

353
00:22:38,100 --> 00:22:40,420
Oh, what's going on here?

354
00:22:40,420 --> 00:22:41,840
Oh dear.

355
00:22:41,840 --> 00:22:43,320
Do you need help?

356
00:22:43,320 --> 00:22:45,453
She must be hot. The patient must be really uncomfortable.

357
00:22:45,453 --> 00:22:47,213
Are you okay?

358
00:22:47,213 --> 00:22:48,627
How about this?

359
00:22:48,627 --> 00:22:51,440
I'll just go to the station with you.

360
00:22:58,633 --> 00:23:00,480
One moment please.

361
00:23:02,580 --> 00:23:03,927
- Bpaa.
- Yes?

362
00:23:03,927 --> 00:23:06,233
Let me handle him quickly, and I'll catch up with you later.

363
00:23:06,233 --> 00:23:07,953
Wait. Who is he?

364
00:23:07,953 --> 00:23:11,380
- What if he finds out where we live?
- It's okay, Bpaa.

365
00:23:11,380 --> 00:23:13,453
I'll be quick.

366
00:23:13,453 --> 00:23:15,893
- We'll talk about it later.
- Okay, take care. I'm off then.

367
00:23:15,893 --> 00:23:17,540
Let's go.

368
00:23:24,520 --> 00:23:27,467
[Bang Mae Nang Police Station]

369
00:23:27,467 --> 00:23:31,020
We reviewed the CCTV footage from the crime scene to nearby areas.

370
00:23:31,020 --> 00:23:33,733
We found that the suspect stopped to refuel at a gas station.

371
00:23:33,733 --> 00:23:37,220
The station staff said the suspect never removed their helmet

372
00:23:37,220 --> 00:23:39,040
so we couldn't get a look at their face.

373
00:23:39,040 --> 00:23:42,980
As for the license plate, it turned out to be fake.

374
00:23:43,573 --> 00:23:48,260
But even if we didn't see the suspect's face, we did get some other key evidence.

375
00:23:48,260 --> 00:23:50,333
What kind of evidence?

376
00:23:50,333 --> 00:23:51,320
The gas station staff said

377
00:23:51,320 --> 00:23:54,273
the suspect had tattoos on the backs of both hands.

378
00:24:08,193 --> 00:24:11,320
Have you ever seen those tattoos before?

379
00:24:12,700 --> 00:24:14,567
No, I haven't.

380
00:24:14,567 --> 00:24:15,813
Are you sure?

381
00:24:15,813 --> 00:24:18,160
You haven't had any personal conflicts with anyone?

382
00:24:18,160 --> 00:24:20,380
As I said the last time I spoke to the police,

383
00:24:20,380 --> 00:24:23,090
I've had some work-related issues with colleagues,

384
00:24:23,093 --> 00:24:26,607
but I don't think they'd go as far as sending someone to hurt me.

385
00:24:27,440 --> 00:24:28,790
But if I had to guess,

386
00:24:28,790 --> 00:24:32,467
it might be a rival company trying to steal information.

387
00:24:32,467 --> 00:24:36,647
So we still don't have enough evidence to identify the suspect.

388
00:24:36,647 --> 00:24:41,240
If we find anything else, we'll contact you right away.

389
00:24:41,240 --> 00:24:43,260
Thank you.

390
00:24:43,260 --> 00:24:45,040
Thank you.

391
00:24:46,440 --> 00:24:47,413
[Police Station for the People]

392
00:24:47,413 --> 00:24:51,487
If the police haven't caught the suspect yet, please be careful.

393
00:24:52,107 --> 00:24:53,853
Thank you.

394
00:24:57,920 --> 00:25:00,120
[Cake is waiting for a CT scan in the same building]

395
00:25:01,980 --> 00:25:03,433
I have to go now.

396
00:25:03,433 --> 00:25:04,600
Okay.

397
00:25:04,600 --> 00:25:05,860
- Ouch...
- Cream?

398
00:25:05,860 --> 00:25:07,700
Khun Cream!

399
00:25:12,060 --> 00:25:15,920
Thank you. It must be from lack of sleep recently.

400
00:25:15,920 --> 00:25:18,407
You really need to rest.

401
00:25:18,407 --> 00:25:20,280
Thank you.

402
00:25:20,280 --> 00:25:22,100
I'll get going.

403
00:25:33,353 --> 00:25:36,620
Hello, Doctor. How is my sister doing?

404
00:25:36,620 --> 00:25:38,190
Since the patient was unconscious for a long time,

405
00:25:38,190 --> 00:25:39,880
there will be some confusion and disorientation.

406
00:25:39,880 --> 00:25:43,407
Her brain and body need time to recover.

407
00:25:43,407 --> 00:25:46,390
For speech and movement,

408
00:25:46,390 --> 00:25:49,040
she'll need ongoing care from a physical therapist.

409
00:25:49,047 --> 00:25:51,793
Is there a chance she'll fully recover?

410
00:25:51,793 --> 00:25:53,573
That, I can't say yet.

411
00:25:53,573 --> 00:25:55,993
It depends on how her body responds.

412
00:25:55,993 --> 00:26:00,413
I'll prescribe additional medication to help boost her strength.

413
00:26:01,080 --> 00:26:02,673
Don't worry, sweetie.

414
00:26:02,673 --> 00:26:05,153
We'll keep taking care of Cake as always.

415
00:26:05,153 --> 00:26:08,253
She will get back to normal.

416
00:26:13,633 --> 00:26:14,827
Kaew.

417
00:26:14,827 --> 00:26:16,867
- Yes?
- Bpaa Su asked you to come eat.

418
00:26:16,867 --> 00:26:19,820
I just finished changing P'Cake's clothes.

419
00:26:41,660 --> 00:26:43,293
Cake.

420
00:26:46,500 --> 00:26:49,060
You need to get better soon.

421
00:26:51,780 --> 00:26:55,453
I've got so many things I want your help with.

422
00:26:59,360 --> 00:27:05,200
When you recover, I'll take you shopping. Your favorite thing.

423
00:27:05,873 --> 00:27:09,240
I'll do anything you want.

424
00:27:11,400 --> 00:27:14,840
If you hadn't gone to work pretending to be me,

425
00:27:14,840 --> 00:27:17,380
you wouldn't be like this.

426
00:27:27,020 --> 00:27:29,480
I'm sorry, Cake.

427
00:27:31,433 --> 00:27:35,240
I'm so sorry for what I did and what caused you to become like this.

428
00:27:39,053 --> 00:27:41,847
I'm so sorry, Cake.

429
00:27:53,160 --> 00:27:57,587
Cake? You can hear me, right?

430
00:27:57,587 --> 00:28:00,793
You hear what I'm saying, don't you, Cake?

431
00:28:00,793 --> 00:28:02,400
Cake.

432
00:28:03,987 --> 00:28:06,840
Come back to your old self soon, okay?

433
00:28:07,727 --> 00:28:10,040
I'll be waiting for you.

434
00:28:21,600 --> 00:28:24,387
[Dreamer]

435
00:28:24,387 --> 00:28:26,607
This is the Whisper of Love mural.

436
00:28:26,607 --> 00:28:29,793
It's a well-known piece with a strong narrative.

437
00:28:29,793 --> 00:28:32,980
I think it's a perfect fit to be showcased on a global level.

438
00:28:32,980 --> 00:28:37,793
I plan to use this as the inspiration for our woven fabric design.

439
00:28:37,793 --> 00:28:41,067
No wonder you were standing there looking at that painting for so long.

440
00:28:41,067 --> 00:28:42,707
I'm okay with that.

441
00:28:42,707 --> 00:28:45,793
It aligns well with the Iconic Thai Designer concept.

442
00:28:45,793 --> 00:28:51,020
But, P'Cream, I think the colors in the painting feel a little flat.

443
00:28:51,020 --> 00:28:56,627
Shouldn't we tweak the tones a bit and make it more fun?

444
00:28:56,627 --> 00:28:59,487
I think the highlight of the special Chok woven fabric

445
00:28:59,487 --> 00:29:02,507
is the variety of weaving techniques in a single piece.

446
00:29:02,507 --> 00:29:05,500
So I believe we should carefully select both the patterns

447
00:29:05,500 --> 00:29:09,253
and core colors to best reflect its identity.

448
00:29:09,253 --> 00:29:13,020
- I get that, but I think...
- I actually agree with Cream.

449
00:29:16,040 --> 00:29:18,613
That would add more value to the fabric.

450
00:29:18,613 --> 00:29:20,527
Less is more.

451
00:29:24,147 --> 00:29:29,100
Whoa, this is the first time P'Min hasn't disagreed with P'Cream.

452
00:29:34,013 --> 00:29:36,467
What about the pattern?

453
00:29:36,467 --> 00:29:38,589
What direction are we going with it?

454
00:29:41,893 --> 00:29:43,440
Khai?

455
00:29:45,447 --> 00:29:47,420
This is from the Fall-Winter collection.

456
00:29:47,420 --> 00:29:49,913
It's the last one that Khun Tul's mom designed.

457
00:29:49,913 --> 00:29:52,020
It was the most unique and bold departure

458
00:29:52,020 --> 00:29:53,260
from Dreamer's usual style.

459
00:29:53,260 --> 00:29:55,170
So I think we should use

460
00:29:55,170 --> 00:29:57,040
this minimalist silhouette and cutting style

461
00:29:57,040 --> 00:29:58,341
as our reference for the competition collection.

462
00:29:58,341 --> 00:30:01,127
I believe it pairs well with the special Chok fabric.

463
00:30:06,320 --> 00:30:09,760
Khun Cream, please draft the fabric layout and send it to me as soon as possible

464
00:30:09,760 --> 00:30:12,320
so I can forward it to the weaving team in Nan.

465
00:30:12,320 --> 00:30:15,340
We don't have much time left to produce the final outfits.

466
00:30:15,340 --> 00:30:16,447
Got it.

467
00:30:16,447 --> 00:30:18,480
Everyone, I'm counting on you.

468
00:30:19,100 --> 00:30:20,660
Sure.

469
00:30:26,960 --> 00:30:29,760
[Nira Fashion House]

470
00:30:35,760 --> 00:30:39,540
By this week, Cream will send the design to the weavers.

471
00:30:39,540 --> 00:30:43,400
In one month, the special Chok fabric will be sent to Dreamer,

472
00:30:43,400 --> 00:30:45,960
so their pattern makers can cut it in time for the competition.

473
00:30:45,960 --> 00:30:49,147
You've done well.

474
00:30:50,227 --> 00:30:53,253
We should've met sooner.

475
00:30:53,253 --> 00:30:58,373
I wouldn't have had to waste money on people who keep screwing up.

476
00:31:01,340 --> 00:31:05,573
From now on, I'll report everything directly to you.

477
00:31:05,573 --> 00:31:07,960
And if our plan succeeds,

478
00:31:07,960 --> 00:31:13,330
I'm sure Nira Fashion House will get into the P&Y group.

479
00:31:13,333 --> 00:31:18,987
If it works out, you'll be handsomely rewarded.

480
00:31:22,520 --> 00:31:24,073
Khun Wasin?

481
00:31:24,073 --> 00:31:25,213
Yes, Khun Cindy?

482
00:31:25,213 --> 00:31:28,893
Once the special Chok fabric is ready, begin immediately.

483
00:31:28,893 --> 00:31:30,553
Understood.

484
00:31:33,467 --> 00:31:36,880
If you're not good at using your brain like Khun Mintra,

485
00:31:36,880 --> 00:31:40,820
you'll just have to do the physical labor.

486
00:31:40,820 --> 00:31:44,307
Because that's the only thing you're good at.

487
00:31:47,087 --> 00:31:49,193
Excellent work.

488
00:31:54,900 --> 00:31:57,040
[Dreamer]

489
00:31:58,780 --> 00:32:00,520
How's it going? Everything okay?

490
00:32:00,520 --> 00:32:02,253
We're still choosing the pattern.

491
00:32:02,253 --> 00:32:04,000
- Okay.
- Cream.

492
00:32:04,000 --> 00:32:05,180
Cream.

493
00:32:05,180 --> 00:32:07,360
I think the adjustments you suggested are actually great.

494
00:32:07,360 --> 00:32:10,073
They'll help better showcase the detail of the Special Chok weave.

495
00:32:10,073 --> 00:32:12,340
So what do you think? Good?

496
00:32:12,340 --> 00:32:13,320
- Good, right?
- Yes.

497
00:32:13,320 --> 00:32:15,047
Let's go with that then.

498
00:32:19,667 --> 00:32:20,680
If there's nothing else,

499
00:32:20,680 --> 00:32:22,710
I'll go finalize the fabric layout. It's due soon.

500
00:32:22,713 --> 00:32:23,993
- Okay.
- Yes.

501
00:32:23,993 --> 00:32:26,127
P'Cream. P'Cream.

502
00:32:26,127 --> 00:32:29,553
I've got the expense report from our Nan trip for you to sign.

503
00:32:29,553 --> 00:32:31,260
Okay.

504
00:32:33,727 --> 00:32:36,120
- Here.
- Oh?

505
00:32:37,913 --> 00:32:39,287
P'Cream, did you change your signature?

506
00:32:39,287 --> 00:32:41,540
I've been meaning to say something.

507
00:32:41,540 --> 00:32:44,680
Your new signature is really pretty.

508
00:32:47,213 --> 00:32:48,807
It doesn't look anything like the old one.

509
00:32:48,807 --> 00:32:51,800
The old one was beautiful too.

510
00:32:56,813 --> 00:33:00,200
A fortune teller told me I had to change it.

511
00:33:00,200 --> 00:33:02,273
Because I had a recent accident and so I had to change it.

512
00:33:02,273 --> 00:33:03,613
Oh, right.

513
00:33:03,613 --> 00:33:04,898
Can I have their contact?

514
00:33:04,898 --> 00:33:07,287
Sure. I'll head back to work now.

515
00:33:07,287 --> 00:33:09,580
- Let's get to work.
- Okay.

516
00:33:14,587 --> 00:33:16,727
Moo? Moo?

517
00:33:16,727 --> 00:33:18,467
- Yes?
- Come here.

518
00:33:18,467 --> 00:33:20,040
Let me see.

519
00:33:24,567 --> 00:33:26,580
What is it, P'Min?

520
00:33:32,913 --> 00:33:36,653
I think ever since the accident, Cream's changed quite a bit.

521
00:33:36,653 --> 00:33:40,227
Back in Nan, her shortness of breath suddenly flared up.

522
00:33:40,227 --> 00:33:42,287
Before that, I'd never seen anything like it.

523
00:33:42,287 --> 00:33:45,380
The driver hit her, which caused brain trauma,

524
00:33:45,380 --> 00:33:46,880
so it's affecting her physically.

525
00:33:46,887 --> 00:33:48,797
That's all.

526
00:33:48,797 --> 00:33:50,153
So are we done yet?

527
00:33:50,153 --> 00:33:52,140
It's so hot...

528
00:34:03,253 --> 00:34:05,313
- Ai Tul.
- Yes?

529
00:34:05,313 --> 00:34:09,213
I brought some location options in Chiang Mai for the new branch. You pick.

530
00:34:09,213 --> 00:34:11,120
Here. This is the first one.

531
00:34:11,120 --> 00:34:14,140
It's near Nimman and close to shopping districts.

532
00:34:14,140 --> 00:34:17,607
I think this one, if we renovate a little, will be beautiful.

533
00:34:17,607 --> 00:34:19,840
- And this is the second.
- Wait, wait, wait, wait.

534
00:34:19,840 --> 00:34:21,400
Go back a bit. What's that?

535
00:34:24,000 --> 00:34:27,140
[Wonderful Slim]

536
00:34:31,400 --> 00:34:33,640
[Wonderful Slim]
[Body Cream Fit Slim - Slimming Cream]

537
00:34:35,000 --> 00:34:37,393
What's that Wonderful Slim building?

538
00:34:37,393 --> 00:34:40,340
The most famous weight loss clinic in Chiang Mai.

539
00:34:40,340 --> 00:34:42,173
- Chiang Mai?
- Yes.

540
00:34:42,173 --> 00:34:43,333
Does it have any other branches?

541
00:34:43,333 --> 00:34:46,200
Only one, in Chiang Mai. Why?

542
00:34:48,800 --> 00:34:51,600
Don't tell me you've been a client there.

543
00:34:51,600 --> 00:34:54,147
Is that how your body looks so good? Got some help, did you?

544
00:34:54,147 --> 00:34:56,020
No, it's not that.

545
00:34:56,947 --> 00:34:59,680
I saw medication in Khun Cream's bag.

546
00:34:59,680 --> 00:35:01,300
It's from this clinic.

547
00:35:01,847 --> 00:35:05,287
If you're saying there's only one branch in Chiang Mai,

548
00:35:05,287 --> 00:35:06,893
then where did she get the meds from?

549
00:35:06,893 --> 00:35:08,247
What's so strange about that?

550
00:35:08,247 --> 00:35:10,667
Can't she just order online?

551
00:35:10,667 --> 00:35:15,367
Why are you so suspicious over something so small?

552
00:35:15,367 --> 00:35:17,427
You really care, right?

553
00:35:17,427 --> 00:35:20,420
You got a crush on her?

554
00:35:21,420 --> 00:35:22,940
Yes.

555
00:35:22,940 --> 00:35:25,580
- I already told her I like her.
- What? (lit.: Are you crazy?)

556
00:35:25,580 --> 00:35:27,320
So it's not a crush. You actually confessed?

557
00:35:27,320 --> 00:35:29,340
- Yes.
- And? What now?

558
00:35:29,340 --> 00:35:32,180
- She hasn't replied.
- Oh...

559
00:35:32,180 --> 00:35:34,220
But I told her it's okay. No need to rush.

560
00:35:34,220 --> 00:35:36,060
- I just...
- What?

561
00:35:36,060 --> 00:35:38,093
I have this feeling.

562
00:35:38,093 --> 00:35:40,687
As if she's hiding something from me.

563
00:35:40,687 --> 00:35:42,380
Over some medication?

564
00:35:42,380 --> 00:35:43,980
What are your suspecting her of?

565
00:35:43,980 --> 00:35:45,213
Come on, she's a woman.

566
00:35:45,213 --> 00:35:48,593
She probably just wants to keep in shape like everyone else.

567
00:35:48,593 --> 00:35:51,960
You're overthinking again. You're stressed from work, man.

568
00:35:51,960 --> 00:35:54,600
- Yes.
- So?

569
00:35:54,600 --> 00:35:56,533
Which location are you picking?

570
00:35:56,533 --> 00:35:58,520
I'll decide later.

571
00:35:59,120 --> 00:36:02,920
You're quick to confess your love, but slow to make work decisions, huh?

572
00:36:03,893 --> 00:36:06,747
- Make sure to make it soon.
- Yes.

573
00:36:53,793 --> 00:36:56,140
Everyone's gone home already?

574
00:36:57,087 --> 00:36:59,160
Guess I'll head home too.

575
00:37:09,800 --> 00:37:12,240
Khun Tul.

576
00:37:12,240 --> 00:37:14,193
Want to grab dinner first?

577
00:37:17,147 --> 00:37:19,493
I thought you'd gone home already.

578
00:37:20,520 --> 00:37:22,980
I was just clearing some work too.

579
00:37:22,980 --> 00:37:26,300
Ever since we got back from Nan, it's been piling up like a mountain, Khun Cream.

580
00:37:26,300 --> 00:37:29,180
Here. Let's eat together.

581
00:37:30,353 --> 00:37:32,550
So you stayed this late not to work,

582
00:37:32,550 --> 00:37:34,700
but to find someone to eat with?

583
00:37:36,253 --> 00:37:38,640
There's still a lot left to do, you know.

584
00:37:38,640 --> 00:37:41,933
So? What's in here?

585
00:37:42,787 --> 00:37:46,220
Normally, when you're busy like this,

586
00:37:46,220 --> 00:37:48,780
don't you usually take your work home?

587
00:37:51,400 --> 00:37:53,327
Okay, fine.

588
00:37:53,327 --> 00:37:54,967
I just wanted to keep you company.

589
00:37:54,967 --> 00:37:58,147
I've seen you working late several nights now.

590
00:37:58,147 --> 00:38:02,920
If anything happened again, who'd take care of you?

591
00:38:04,040 --> 00:38:05,442
Thank you.

592
00:38:05,442 --> 00:38:08,753
Here, let's eat, shall we?

593
00:38:08,753 --> 00:38:12,287
Thanks so much,

594
00:38:12,287 --> 00:38:17,780
I have to confess. After 6 p.m., I can't eat anything anymore.

595
00:38:18,700 --> 00:38:20,913
Guess I'll have to eat it all myself, huh?

596
00:38:20,913 --> 00:38:23,240
Still two full boxes.

597
00:38:26,087 --> 00:38:30,320
I never realized you were so strict about food.

598
00:38:31,180 --> 00:38:36,407
Before the accident, you weren't like this at all.

599
00:38:36,407 --> 00:38:40,070
Well, after I got discharged from the hospital,

600
00:38:40,070 --> 00:38:43,130
my health hasn't been the same.

601
00:38:43,133 --> 00:38:45,380
So I have to take better care of myself now.

602
00:38:46,393 --> 00:38:48,820
That's great, Khun Cream.

603
00:38:48,820 --> 00:38:54,407
Also, when you fainted in Nan, I saw in your bag.

604
00:38:54,407 --> 00:38:57,147
You had a bunch of weight loss supplements from a slimming center.

605
00:38:57,147 --> 00:39:00,660
So when did you start the program?

606
00:39:03,318 --> 00:39:06,140
I didn't actually join it.

607
00:39:06,140 --> 00:39:07,900
It was a friend.

608
00:39:07,900 --> 00:39:14,073
My friend did, and then she recommended it to me, and gave me a bit to try.

609
00:39:14,073 --> 00:39:19,520
When it worked well, I just kept ordering it.

610
00:39:19,520 --> 00:39:22,980
Khun Cream, isn't that kind of dangerous?

611
00:39:29,127 --> 00:39:31,747
I'm sorry if I'm being a little too nosy.

612
00:39:32,633 --> 00:39:38,147
But Khun Cream, you're not just important to the company.

613
00:39:44,413 --> 00:39:47,113
You're important to me, toom Khun Cream.

614
00:39:49,127 --> 00:39:51,340
I really worry about you.

615
00:40:02,380 --> 00:40:04,380
Thank you.

616
00:40:07,307 --> 00:40:11,107
I... I'm heading home.

617
00:40:11,107 --> 00:40:12,767
Okay.

618
00:40:12,767 --> 00:40:14,880
See you tomorrow.

619
00:40:14,880 --> 00:40:16,760
See you tomorrow.

620
00:40:18,967 --> 00:40:21,387
Make sure to finish it, okay?

621
00:40:21,387 --> 00:40:23,800
Yes. Thanks.

622
00:40:41,440 --> 00:40:43,120
Pete.

623
00:40:46,167 --> 00:40:48,033
Katie.

624
00:40:49,520 --> 00:40:51,240
Katie, what?

625
00:40:51,240 --> 00:40:53,307
Pete, what's going on?

626
00:40:54,160 --> 00:40:56,073
What do you mean?

627
00:40:56,073 --> 00:40:59,340
You're not usually like this.

628
00:40:59,340 --> 00:41:00,993
Like what?

629
00:41:02,918 --> 00:41:05,447
Sorry Katie, I'm not really up for it tonight.

630
00:41:05,447 --> 00:41:07,833
Why don't you go hang out with your friends?

631
00:41:10,487 --> 00:41:12,727
And next time, don't call me again.

632
00:41:20,053 --> 00:41:22,113
I've arrived, Khun Wasin.

633
00:41:28,313 --> 00:41:30,240
The gas station attendant said the suspect

634
00:41:30,240 --> 00:41:32,260
had tattoos on the back of both hands.

635
00:42:49,913 --> 00:42:51,427
Gosh.

636
00:43:00,667 --> 00:43:02,820
Did anyone recognize your face?

637
00:43:03,607 --> 00:43:05,347
I'm not sure.

638
00:43:05,347 --> 00:43:07,773
But the store had security cameras.

639
00:43:08,693 --> 00:43:10,467
Then get out of there!

640
00:43:10,467 --> 00:43:12,513
Don't come back until I say so.

641
00:43:12,513 --> 00:43:14,480
I'll handle this myself.

642
00:43:15,287 --> 00:43:16,960
Yes, Sir.

643
00:43:30,607 --> 00:43:33,707
Kamol. I need your help.

644
00:43:35,960 --> 00:43:37,930
I really apologize,

645
00:43:37,930 --> 00:43:41,290
but all the cameras in our store are broken.

646
00:43:42,033 --> 00:43:43,533
Really?

647
00:43:43,533 --> 00:43:45,600
Not a single one is working?

648
00:43:45,600 --> 00:43:48,507
None. I'm really sorry.

649
00:43:50,013 --> 00:43:51,740
All right.

650
00:43:51,740 --> 00:43:53,480
Thanks a lot, Khun Kamol.

651
00:43:53,480 --> 00:43:55,027
Sure.

652
00:44:05,647 --> 00:44:08,220
All set, Phi.

653
00:44:08,227 --> 00:44:11,727
Thanks, Kamol. I'll transfer the money now.

654
00:44:21,113 --> 00:44:23,100
Clench your hand.

655
00:44:23,100 --> 00:44:25,293
Open your palm.

656
00:44:25,293 --> 00:44:27,260
It's okay. Take it slow.

657
00:44:27,260 --> 00:44:29,480
You're doing really well.

658
00:44:29,487 --> 00:44:31,707
Clench your hand.

659
00:44:31,707 --> 00:44:33,800
Open your palm.

660
00:44:34,687 --> 00:44:36,893
Very good.

661
00:44:36,893 --> 00:44:38,670
That's enough for today.

662
00:44:38,670 --> 00:44:41,030
Let's not overdo it since we're just starting.

663
00:44:41,867 --> 00:44:44,633
Something like this, okay? Try to keep doing this every day.

664
00:44:44,633 --> 00:44:48,187
If I'm not on shift, I'll come help again.

665
00:44:48,187 --> 00:44:52,373
Thank you so much. Really, thank you.

666
00:44:52,373 --> 00:44:54,820
Let me give you a ride home today.

667
00:44:54,820 --> 00:44:56,493
Looks like it's about to rain.

668
00:44:56,493 --> 00:44:58,280
All right, let's go.

669
00:44:58,280 --> 00:45:00,767
Thanks, Phi.

670
00:45:00,767 --> 00:45:03,733
- Can you help close the gate, Dear?
- Okay.

671
00:45:05,927 --> 00:45:07,613
Cake.

672
00:45:08,333 --> 00:45:11,933
You did amazing today. You were really great.

673
00:45:11,933 --> 00:45:15,680
If you keep this up every day, you'll recover in no time.

674
00:45:21,893 --> 00:45:24,127
Do you want to tell me something?

675
00:45:24,127 --> 00:45:25,740
Well?

676
00:45:26,733 --> 00:45:28,753
No more training.

677
00:45:28,753 --> 00:45:31,440
You've done so much already. That's more than enough for today.

678
00:45:31,440 --> 00:45:34,087
We'll do more another day, okay?

679
00:46:18,813 --> 00:46:20,147
- P'Cream.
- What?

680
00:46:20,147 --> 00:46:22,540
Khun Pete's waiting outside the house.
